The Speaker of the House of Representatives Femi Gbajabiamila has joined other personalities in congratulating Nigerians for witnessing the country’s 60th Independence Anniversary. Gbajabiamila said Nigeria has come a long way and has overcome many challenges in the past 60 years, noting that “things are going to get better.” In a goodwill message to mark Nigeria’s 60th Independence Anniversary, the Speaker eulogised and paid glowing tributes to Nigeria’s heroes, who made sacrifices for the country to become what it is today. Amidst a myriad of challenges, Gbajabiamila said Nigerians are the ones that will save the country and help her to attain lofty heights. The Speaker said Nigeria is on a forward march to greatness and would not turn back, no matter the obstacles encountered.